profile_default/
ipython_config.py

# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1263, we should ignore Pipfile.lock as it is generated.
#   Alternatively, check this in if you want to deploy this as an app:
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, ignore poetry.lock in libraries, but keep in applications:
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, ignore pdm.lock in libraries, but keep in applications:
# pdm.lock

